define("_HELP_USKOLAXGALLERY_BONUS",			 	'<b>Bonus:</b><br>Here you will encounter special options and sites that will further enhance your Galeria.');
define("_HELP_USKOLAXGALLERY_INFO",			 		'<b>Gallery Info:</b><br>Here is where you define the title (graphics or text format) and basic display elements for each gallery. Select whether comments and ranking should be allowed, and various display options. Note that this is for each gallery, because you may want one gallery to have comments, others appear with ranking only, each individually specified.');
define("_HELP_USKOLAXGALLERY_ID",			 		'<b>ID:</b><br>This is the internal identification (key) of each gallery. Administrators only need to know it to delete the gallery.');
define("_HELP_USKOLAXGALLERY_PROBARTEMAS",		 	'<b>Try Our Galeria Stylesheets:<br>Click to jump down to the Galeria Stylesheets, our exclusive pre-configured presentation stylesheets.<br> Here you can load the themes that define all the important parameters for all aspects of a gallery presentation. <br>It is helpful to preload the parameters from a Galeria Stylesheet for a gallery, then adjust to your needs and save as a unique Galeria Stylesheet name for use with your other galleries.');
define("_HELP_USKOLAXGALLERY_NOMBRECARPETA",		'<b>Folder Name:</b><br>Enter the name of the folder where you will store your images on the server. Do not change the name of the folder, you will lose the information submitted about the photos, which is stored with your original gallery name.');
define("_HELP_USKOLAXGALLERY_FOTODESC",		 	 	'<b>Description:</b><br>This is the text that describes the gallery to the users in case the Large and Small Title graphics are not specified. Also, it is the description that is shown with the gallery ID for selection by the administrator.');
define("_HELP_USKOLAXGALLERY_GRANDE",		 	 	'<b>Large Title Graphic:</b><br>This is the large image that represents the gallery when the Large Photo is viewed. This graphic as also used as a selection button when viewing all galleries in the opening page.');
define("_HELP_USKOLAXGALLERY_FOTOPEQUENA",		 	'<b>Small Title Graphic:</b><br>This is the image that replaces the text title of the gallery when the user views the Thumbnails, and is also the image that is shown in the block.<p align=left>This image also serves as a button to other galleries when the user is viewing the thumbnails page.');
define("_HELP_USKOLAXGALLERY_PERMITIRENVIOSDE",		'<b>Allow submission of:</b><br>Select the options that the users will be allowed to perform FOR THIS GALLERY.');
define("_HELP_USKOLAXGALLERY_PERMITIDOSUBIRCOMENTARIOS", '<b>Allow COMMENTS to be submitted:</b><br>Check this option to allow the users to SUBMIT COMMENTS about the images in this gallery.');
define("_HELP_USKOLAXGALLERY_PERMITIDOSUBIRVOTACIONES",  '<b>Allow VOTES to be submitted:</b><br>Check this option to allow the users to VOTE from 1 to 10 on the images in this gallery.');
define("_HELP_USKOLAXGALLERY_PERMITIDOSUBIRFICHEROS",	 '<b>Allow IMAGES to be submitted:</b><br>Check this option to allow users to SUBMIT THEIR OWN IMAGES to this gallery. A submission box will appear with places for their title, description, keywords and Photo By fields. Their registered username (or Anonymous) will automatically be used as the Submitted By field, and the date submitted is automatically captured. The images are stored in your gallery folder, subfolder /big. You may then wish to manually create a small image to be used in the block and in the thumbnails, which is stored in your gallery folder, sub folder /small.');
define("_HELP_USKOLAXGALLERY_TAMANOMAXIMO",	   	 	'<b>Maximum File Size</b><br>Establishes the maximum size in bytes that is permitted for images submitted to the server.<br> Put 0 if there is no size limit.');
define("_HELP_USKOLAXGALLERY_VISUALIZAR",	 	 	'<b>Display Options:</b><br>Control the display any of these counters with the images.');
define("_HELP_USKOLAXGALLERY_PERMITIDOVERVISITAS",	'<b>Display Visitors:</b><br>Check this option to allow the visitors to see the number of views for each image.');
define("_HELP_USKOLAXGALLERY_PERMITIDOVERFECHA",	'<b>Display Date Submitted:</b><br>check this option to display the dates the images were submitted to the gallery.');
define("_HELP_USKOLAXGALLERY_VERXOOPSTEMA",		 	'<b>Use Xoops Themes First:</b><br>This is a powerful option with many uses for experienced designers.<P align=left>There are three options regarding the themes.<br><ul>1. Do not check this option if you wish to use the Galeria Stylesheet presets for this gallery, stored in uskolaxgallery/icons/[Galeria Picture Frame Style]. (the most common)<p align=left>2. Check this option if you wish the Galeria to look first in the Xoops themes for picture frame images.<br><p align=left>3. If you check this option, Galeria will always try to load the Picture Frame Style images from the folder xoops/themes/[themename]/[galeriastyle] first if the folder exists.  If the style folder does not exist, no border images will be loaded!<br></ul><p align=left>Explanation with practical examples: <br><ul>A. Suppose we just installed Galeria want the users to see the gallery with the 3DBasic Picture Frame Style. (note: The Galeria Stylesheets to load can be selected below). In this case, do not select the option to Use Xoops Themes First.<br><P align=left>B. Suppose we want the Galeria to change the theme depending on the Xoops theme that the user has selected. Then we check the option Use the Xoops Themes First, and copy the contents of the icons/[Galeria Picture Frame Style]/ folder into xoops/themes/[selectedtheme]/images (we want to create a structure like xoops/themes/[theme]/images/big and xoops/themes/[theme]/images/small.<br> <P align=left>C. Suppose we want more control of the frame styles that are seen when the gallery is loaded. We could select the Galeria picture frame style that is going to show when the user is using every Xoops theme. This option comes in handy when we see that some of the styles do not coordinate with some of the Xoops themes you allow the user to select.  For those particular Xoops themes, place a more appropriate picture frame style in the folder xoops/themes/[xoopsTheme]/[Galeria Picture Frame Style].</ul>');
define("_HELP_USKOLAXGALLERY_GUARDARCAMBIOSGALERIA",'<b>Save Changes to Galeria:</b><br>Saves the changes you make anywhere on this page to the database for this gallery.');
